543	// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
544	// Shell command intent classification
545	//
546	// Every classifier (reads, searches, lists, writes) operates on the same
547	// tokenized + segment-split representation. This keeps quoting, flag handling,
548	// and redirection logic in one place instead of N independent regexes over
549	// the raw command string — which previously mis-extracted paths for commands
550	// like `cat -n foo`, `head -n 20 foo`, `find -L /path`, and was fooled by
551	// operator-looking characters inside quoted arguments.
552	// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
